fields.value: Single Incision Device (TVT Secur) Versus Retropubic Tension-free Vaginal Tape Device (TVT) for the Management of Stress Urinary Incontinence in Women: A Randomized Clinical Trial
Tension-free Vaginal Tape Management of Stress Incontinence in Women: Randomized Trial of TVT Secur Versus TVT

dsDescriptionValue.value: The objective of this Canadian multi-centre pragmatic randomized controlled trial was to compare the effectiveness of the new single-incision device, Gynecare TVT Secur, to the established predecate retropubic TVT device, in terms of objective cure of stress urinary incontinence (SUI) at 12 months postoperatively. Other outcomes included: complications, symptoms, and incontinence-related quality of life.

publicationCitation.value: Ross S, Tang S, Schulz J, et al. Single incision device (TVT Secur) versus retropubic tension-free vaginal tape device (TVT) for the management of stress urinary incontinence in women: a randomized clinical trial. BMC Research Notes. 2014;7:941.

fields.value: Calgary, Alberta; Edmonton, Alberta; Penticton, British Columbia; Vancouver, British Columbia

grantNumberAgency.value: Johnson & Johnson Medical Companies; Alberta Health Services; Women's and Children's Health Research Institute (WCHRI)

value: Ross S, Robert M, Ducey A.  The short life cycle of a surgical device - literature analysis using McKinlay's 7-stage model.  Health Policy Technol. 2015 Feb 23;4:168-188.

Urogenital Distress Inventory (UDI-6); Incontinence Impact Questionnaire (IIQ-7); the Pelvic Organ Prolapse/Urinary Incontinence Sexual Questionnaire-12, (PISQ-12); the 15D Instrument of Health-related Quality of Life (15D) was included for the proposed economic evaluation which was never done.

otherGeographicCoverage.value: Calgary, Alberta; Edmonton, Alberta; Vancouver, British Columbia; Penticton, British Columbia

value: Women with stress incontinence, defined as leaking with increased abdominal pressure.

fields.value: Data was collected at baseline and one year postoperative.

The sample size estimate for our trial was 300, but the trial stopped early because of poor recruitment. 74 women participated (40 allocated to TVT Secur, 34 to TVT). Data was collected and analysed for 33/40 (83%) of the TVT Secur group and 28/34 (89%) of the TVT group.
Self-administered questionnaire: Paper; Self-administered writings and/or diaries; Physical measurements and tests; Chart review
The trial ended early because of poor recruitment.

Emails were sent out two months before the year follow-up to schedule the appointment and reminders were sent one month before the appointment. If the participant was unable to come in person, questionnaires were sent by mail. Additional contacts were collected for study participants in the event that they were hard to reach or had moved.

The data entry clerk entered data, and the statistician and data entry clerk checked over all data before analysis. Data was checked for outliers, and range and logic checks were performed. Paper forms were kept and were compared to electronic records in the event of missing or outlying data.
